What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Flavored Butter Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Flavored Butter Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the global flavored butter market will project a CAGR of 3.2% for the forecast period of 2021-2028. Growth and expansion of the food and beverages industry, ever-rising population around the globe, rising consumer consciousness towards high quality and nutritional food items, surging preferences towards home baking cultures in the developing economies and increasing personal disposable income by the major companies are the major factors attributable to the growth of flavored butter market. Therefore, the market value, which was USD 1.21 billion in 2020, would rocket up to USD 1.55 billion by 2028.

Butter is prepared using pasteurized cream that is obtained from milk products. From the name itself, it is clear that flavored butter is either sweetened or salted butter that is generally consumed to enhance the taste and mouth feel. Not just that, the butter flavours enhance the overall look and feel of the product.

Shifting tastes and preferences and rising globalization are the major factors fostering the growth of the market. Changing and evolving lifestyle, growth in the penetration of e-commerce platforms especially in the developing economies, growing influence of western cuisine along with rising number of restaurants, hotels and cafes and rising focus of the manufacturers on the launch of new and innovative products are other important factors acting as market growth determinants. Rising expenditure to undertake research and development proficiencies, surging demand for ingredients which add value to the final product and rise in the overall milk and dairy industry globally will further induce growth in the market value.

However, large scale prevalence of overweight and obese population will pose a major challenge to the growth of the market. Growing incidences of diabetes and limited intake of butter recommended by physician will also hamper the market growth rate. Growing negative perception towards saturated fats and high cholesterol food items will yet again derail the market growth rate.

